Label: head of government
Description: head of the executive power of this town, city, municipality, state, country, or other governmental body

Label: video
Description: relevant video. For images, use the property P18. For film trailers, qualify with "object has role" (P3831)="trailer" (Q622550)

Label: traffic sign
Description: graphic symbol describing the item, used at the side of or above roads to give instructions or provide information to road users

Label: route map
Description: image of route map at Wikimedia Commons

Label: transport network
Description: network the infrastructure is a part of

Label: country
Description: sovereign state that this item is in (not to be used for human beings)

Label: image
Description: image of relevant illustration of the subject; if available, also use more specific properties (sample: coat of arms image, locator map, flag image, signature image, logo image, collage image)

Label: place of birth
Description: most specific known birth location of a person, animal or fictional character

Label: place of death
Description: most specific known (e.g. city instead of country, or hospital instead of city) death location of a person, animal or fictional character

Label: sex or gender
Description: sex or gender identity of human or animal. For human: male, female, non-binary, intersex, transgender female, transgender male, agender, etc. For animal: male organism, female organism. Groups of same gender use subclass of (P279)

Label: father
Description: male parent of the subject. For stepfather, use  "stepparent" (P3448)

Label: mother
Description: female parent of the subject. For stepmother, use "stepparent" (P3448)

Label: spouse
Description: the subject has the object as their spouse (husband, wife, partner, etc.)

Label: country of citizenship
Description: the object is a country that recognizes the subject as its citizen

Label: continent
Description: continent of which the subject is a part

Label: instance of
Description: that class of which this subject is a particular example and member

Label: head of state
Description: official with the highest formal authority in a country/state

Label: capital
Description: seat of government of a country, province, state or other type of administrative territorial entity

Label: official language
Description: language designated as official by this item

Label: currency
Description: currency used by item

Label: position held
Description: subject currently or formerly holds the object position or public office

Label: child
Description: subject has object as child. Do not use for stepchildrenâ€”use "relative" (P1038), etc.

Label: flag image
Description: image of the item's flag

Label: shares border with
Description: countries or administrative subdivisions, of equal level, that this item borders

Label: author
Description: main creator(s) of a written work

Label: audio
Description: relevant sound. If available, use a more specific property. Samples: "spoken text audio" etc.

Label: family
Description: family, including dynasty and nobility houses. Not family name (use P734 for family name).

Label: member of sports team
Description: sports teams or clubs that the subject represents or represented

Label: director
Description: director(s) of film, TV- series, stageplay, video game or similar

Label: screenwriter
Description: person(s) who wrote the script for subject item

Label: constellation
Description: the area of the celestial sphere of which the subject is a part (from a scientific standpoint...

Label: discoverer or inventor
Description: subject who discovered, first described, invented, or developed this discovery or invention or sci...

Label: site of astronomical discovery
Description: the place where an astronomical object was discovered (observatory, satellite)

Label: ancestral home
Description: place of origin for ancestors of subject

Label: educated at
Description: educational institution attended by subject

Label: top-level Internet domain
Description: Internet domain name system top-level code

Label: connecting line
Description: railway line( s ) subject is directly connected to

Label: architect
Description: person or architectural firm responsible for designing this building

Label: anthem
Description: subject' s official anthem

Label: composer
Description: person( s ) who wrote the music [for lyricist, use "lyrics by" ( P676 ) ]

Label: librettist
Description: author of the libretto (words) of an opera, operetta, oratorio or cantata, or of the book of a musical

Label: commissioned by
Description: person or organization that commissioned this work

Label: sexual orientation
Description: the sexual orientation of the person relative to their declared gender

Label: main regulatory text
Description: text setting the main rules by which the subject is regulated

Label: coat of arms image
Description: "image of the item'coat of arms - for the shield part only use P4004"

Label: noble title
Description: titles held by the person

Label: editor
Description: person who checks and corrects a work (such as a book, newspaper, academic journal, etc.)

Label: field of work
Description: specialization of a person or organization; see P106 for the occupation

Label: member of political party
Description: the political party of which a person is or has been a member or otherwise affiliated

Label: native language
Description: language or languages a person has learned from early childhood
